The '''kallil-virus''' was a virus distinguished by the way in which it clumped together as a jelly-like mass.<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|II|196|Kallil-virus}}</ref> It was notorious for the way that it trembled when touched. When activated, an orb of spores made from the [[malvil-tree]] [[Malubi]], used by a [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] named [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]]<ref name="Fett">''[[Boba Fett: A New Threat]]''</ref> in [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]],<ref name="ERC">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]''</ref> produced a substance that trembled like the virus.<ref name="Fett" />

==Behind the scenes==
The kallil-virus was mentioned in the [[2004]] young reader novel ''[[Boba Fett: A New Threat]]'' by [[Elizabeth Hand]],<ref name="Fett" /> set between the chronologically [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|second]] and [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|third]] ''[[Star Wars]]'' films.<ref name="ERC" /> Within the context of that novel, exactly what kind of thing the kallil-virus was was ambiguous,<ref name="Fett" /> but, in [[2008]], ''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]'' included an entry on the subject that identified it definitively as a [[Wikipedia:Virus|virus]].<ref name="CSWE" />

